Pretoria - A livid Eersterust family is calling on the Department of Health to reprimand the Mamelodi Day Hospital.

 

 This after 76-year-old Martha Marais was allegedly tied to the benches of the waiting area. 

 

 Nursing staff at the Mamelodi Hospital allegedly tied her hands behind her back and to the metal chairs, forcing her on to the cold floor since Tuesday night.

  

 The family said the nursing staff ignored her, and opted to tie her up.

 

 Eyewitness said that Marais was showing signs of excruciating pain and screaming for the nurses to help. 

 

 
  







