   Martha Marais tied to the benches of the waiting area at Mamelodi Day Hospital. Video: Supplied
  
 

 “She was pacing up and down. 

 

 "The old women was in pain,” said an eyewitness.

 

 Marias was referred by the Eersterust clinic to Mamelodi Day Hospital as she needed urgent medical attention.

 

 The hospital caters for patients from Mamelodi, Nellmapius, Eersterust, East Lynne, Cullinan, Pretoria East, Nkangala and Bronkhorstspruit.

 

 The Health Department is yet to comment on the questions posed by the Pretoria News. 

 

 This not the first time the hospital is in hot water. 

 

 In 2017 Reports of patients lying on the floor and in the storage rooms or sitting on casualty benches because of a lack of beds surfaced.

 

 Pretoria News